<item>
            <title>[LU-16967] Split LNDs into sub-packages so MOFED and in-kernel OFED can co-exist in the same repo</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16967</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For large / diverse environments a mix of in-kernel and mofed (and possibly other LNDs) would like to co-exist in a single repo with the same version of lustre.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Current MOFED ko2iblnd and in-kernel ko2iblnd conflict, put them in separate packages so the can be installed independently.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To be consistent place all the LNDs into separate packages.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Enable this feature using --with lndpkgs&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
